[0m[49m[38;5;9m-  9   [0m:[38;5;9m[49m - **L97** — TODO: expert review (S4) recommended adding a short paragraph here on input-side prompt-injection risk. When clinical note content originates from weakly controlled channels (patient portal messages, OCR of faxed outside records, external referrals), an adversarial string in a note field could attempt to override the grounding constraint and instruct the model to fabricate claims or cite nonexistent literature. The suggested mitigation is configuring Bedrock Guardrails with input-side prompt-attack filters in addition to output filters, and treating EHR-sourced structured data and free-text narrative content as different trust tiers.
